The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Monday, June 28, 2004 				 RSS jibe
																								New Delhi, June 27 (PTI): RSS chief K.S. Sudarshan today condemned the central governments move to detoxify NCERT history textbooks. 																								He also called communists traitors and charged them with defaming the Hindu culture. Slamming them as informers of the British, Sudarshan defended the NDA governments attempt to correct the textbooks. It was trying to incorporate the latest research and knowledge, the RSS chief said. 
